As can be seen from the results obtained, the most active substances were symmetric derivatives with an aliphatic spacer. It should be noted that the toxicity of compounds strongly depends on spacer length. In this regard, compounds 3b, c with –C6H12- and –C8H16-linkers, respectively, possess lowest toxicity (CTD50
 = 1712 and 553 μM, correspondingly). Compound 3d appeared to be the most effective, having low EC50 and high CTD50 and SI; the latter exceeded SI for reference compounds 10-fold and more (Table 1
).
